'''Chiara Ferragni''' ({{IPA|it|ˈkjaːra ferˈraɲɲi|lang}}; born 7 May 1987) is an Italian [[Internet celebrity|blogger]], businesswoman, fashion designer and model who has collaborated with fashion and beauty brands<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://fashionmagazine.com/beauty/pantene-chiara-ferragni/ |title=The Blonde Salad's Chiara Ferragni is Pantene's new Global Ambassador|date=26 January 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/fashion/fashion-news/news/a42766/chiara-feraggni-for-tods/ |title=CHIARA FERRAGNI REDESIGNS TWO ICONIC ACCESSORIES FOR A LUXURY ITALIAN LABEL|date=18 July 2017 }}</ref> through her blog ''The Blonde Salad''. <ref name="as">{{Cite web |url=http://www.graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/news/the-blonde-salad-blogger-for-guess-christmas-campaign |title=From Blogger To Model: The Blonde Salad Lands Guess' Christmas Campaign |last=Vince, Jessica |date=10 December 2013 |website=[[Grazia]] |access-date=12 December 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215171401/http://www.graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/news/the-blonde-salad-blogger-for-guess-christmas-campaign |archive-date=15 December 2013 }}</ref>

== Biography ==
Ferragni was born in the northern city of [[Cremona]] in 1987.<ref>Rebecca Arnold, ''30-Second Fashion: The 50 key modes, garments, and designers'' (Ivy Press, 2017), p. 132</ref> Ferragni is the oldest of three daughters of a dentist from Cremona. Her mother [[Marina Di Guardo]] is an Italian writer from [[Sicily]] who also worked as deputy director of the Blumarine fashion house.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fiamma Sanò |date=1 February 2015 |title=Così è nato il fenomeno Ferragni |url=http://www.grazia.it/stile-di-vita/interviste/cosi-e-nato-il-fenomeno-ferragni |access-date=9 January 2016 |website=Grazia}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Latilla |first=Antonella |date=2018-09-01 |title=Perché Chiara Ferragni e Fedez si sono sposati a Noto, in Sicilia |url=https://www.gossipetv.com/chiara-ferragni-fedez-perche-matrimonio-in-sicilia-noto-370363 |access-date=2021-05-20 |website=Gossip e Tv |language=it-IT}}</ref>

At the age of 16, she was hired by the Beatrice model agency in [[Milan]]. She modeled for the agency for a couple of years and then quit, due to "other goals to reach in my life".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.popsugar.com/fashion/photo-gallery/40807847/embed/40808372/Two-Even-Share-Dog-Matilda | title=The Two Even Share a Dog, Matilda | date=9 April 2016 }}</ref> She started her fashion [[blog]] "The Blonde Salad" in October 2009 with an ex-boyfriend, Riccardo Pozzoli.<ref>Paola Paoloni, Rosa Lombardi, ''Advances in Gender and Cultural Research in Business and Economics'' (Springer, 2018), p. 294</ref> In December 2011, she was profiled as the Blogger of the Moment in ''[[Teen Vogue]]'', while a law student at [[Bocconi University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/careers/fashion-careers/2011-06/the-blonde-salad-blogger-profile/ |title=Blogger Of The Moment: The Blonde Salad |last=Frankfort, Lauren |date=December 2011 |website=[[Teen Vogue]] |access-date=12 December 2013 |archive-date=12 D

